## Versioning

- `<runner> version:patch` — Bump patch version (0.0.x)
- `<runner> version:minor` — Bump minor version (0.x.0)
- `<runner> version:major` — Bump major version (x.0.0)

Note: Version scripts should run quality checks BEFORE bumping to prevent broken releases.

---

## Releasing (Fully Automated)

1. Bump version: `<runner> version:patch` (or minor/major)
2. Commit: `git commit -am "chore: bump version to X.Y.Z"`
3. Push: `git push`
4. **Done!** GitHub Actions handles the rest automatically

**What happens automatically:**
- CI workflow runs (lint, typecheck, tests, build)
- Auto Release workflow creates & pushes tag
- Release workflow creates GitHub release

